This paper deals with the problem of corrupted sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of convex optimization techniques (cs.DS) and the analysis of probability distributions (cs.NA). Finally, the numerical experiments involve the implementation of algorithms (cs.SI).
